<subSubSection id="C3079AC0FFE85F58E3DBD928FDEAFC63" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BA2C94BFFE85F58E3DBD928FDEAFC63" blockId="14.[136,1452,630,976]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Etymology:—Δάφνις, from δάφνη–laurel (Greek), in Greek mythology, a beautiful young shepherd in 
<collectingRegion id="49D907A9FFE85F58E72CD928FB07FCAB" box="[1151,1207,810,832]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Sicily</collectingRegion>
and inventor of pastoral songs, the son of Hermes (Mercury). The butterfly 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB2C8FFE85F58E1F7D94CFCC8FC88" baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[676,888,846,867]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Polyommatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="daphnis">
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE85F58E1F7D94CFCC8FC88" box="[676,888,846,867]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Polyommatus daphnis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was named after him. The new 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB2C8FFE85F58E7FBD94CFAE0FC8F" box="[1192,1360,846,868]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE85F58E7FBD94CFAB5FC88" box="[1192,1285,846,867]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Entoloma</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
is named after this butterfly, due to the similar color.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3079AC0FFE85F58E3DBD994FC53FC3B" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA2C94BFFE85F58E3DBD994FC53FC3B" blockId="14.[136,1452,630,976]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Diagnosis:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB2C8FFE85F58E254D994FE08FC40" authorityName="O. V. Morozova, Kovalenko, E. S. Popov &amp; Noordeloos" authorityYear="2022" box="[263,440,918,939]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Entolomataceae" genus="Entoloma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="daphnis">
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE85F58E254D994FE08FC40" box="[263,440,918,939]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Entoloma daphnis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by small pleurotoid basidiomata, small spores with up to the 8 angles, a trichodermal pileipellis (pileus is densely covered by dark blue fibrils) and lack of cheilocystidia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF6299C3FFE85F58E3DBDDDAFD57F7F9" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6608471" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6608471" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6608471/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" startId="14.[136,229,2008,2030]" targetBox="[151,1436,1001,1984]" targetPageId="14">
