<subSubSection id="C3079AC0FFE95F59E3DBD90CFD10FB5F" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA2C94BFFE95F59E3DBD90CFEA8FBEB" blockId="15.[136,1452,782,1385]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Description:— 
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E27DD90CFE0CFCC3" box="[302,444,782,808]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Basidiomata</emphasis>
small, pleurotoid. 
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E1DDD90CFD64FCC3" box="[654,724,782,808]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Pileus</emphasis>
<quantity id="4CE564AEFFE95F59E189D90CFC87FCC2" box="[730,823,782,809]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="3.0">3–7 mm</quantity>
diam., cupulate then reniform with incurved then lobate margin, non hygrophanous, slightly translucently striate, tomentose to finely squamulose, deep blue to dark blue (20D8, 20E7–8). 
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E3AAD954FED1FC9B" box="[249,353,854,880]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Lamellae</emphasis>
moderately distant intermixed with lamellulae, adnate or slightly emarginate, whitish to bluish near the pileal margin then pinkish with concolorous entire edge. 
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E034D979FC2FFC7E" box="[871,927,891,917]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Stipe</emphasis>
3–4 × 
<quantity id="4CE564AEFFE95F59E0BDD978FBD2FC7E" box="[1006,1122,890,917]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="0.75" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5–1 mm</quantity>
, reduced, eccentric or lateral, curved, pruinose to tomentose, concolorous with the pileus or slightly paler (20D7), with white arachnoid mycelial strands at the base attached to the substratum. 
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E1C1D9C1FD59FC36" box="[658,745,963,989]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Context</emphasis>
thin, bluish, under the surface dark blue. 
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E7EED9C0FB48FC37" box="[1213,1272,962,988]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Odor</emphasis>
indistinct, 
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E625D9C1FA1BFC37" box="[1398,1451,963,988]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">taste</emphasis>
not reported.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA2C94BFFE95F59E3EEDE08FD10FB5F" blockId="15.[136,1452,782,1385]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E3EEDE08FEEBFBCF" box="[189,347,1034,1060]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Basidiospores</emphasis>
(7–)8.3(–9) × (5.5–)5.7(–6) μm, Q = (1.3–)1.45(–1.6), heterodiametrical, with 6–8 angles in sideview. 
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E39FDE2CFE92FBA3" box="[204,290,1070,1096]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Basidia</emphasis>
23–31 × 9–12 μm, clavate, clampless. 
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E18EDE2CFC32FBA3" box="[733,898,1070,1096]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Lamellae edge</emphasis>
fertile. 
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E08FDE2CFBCEFBA3" box="[988,1150,1070,1096]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Cheilocystidia</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E7E5DE2CFAE5FBA3" box="[1206,1365,1070,1096]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">pleurocystidia</emphasis>
absent. 
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E3DBDE50FF4AFB87" box="[136,250,1106,1132]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Pileipellis</emphasis>
a trichoderm of long hairs, composed of chains of cylindrical cells narrower at the apical part (27–62 × 5.5–6.5 μm), broader at the base (27–62 × 5.5–6.5 μm) with dark blue intracellular pigment. 
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E799DE74FA15FB7B" box="[1226,1445,1142,1168]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Clamp connections</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E3DBDE98FEFFFB5F" box="[136,335,1178,1204]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">oleiferous hyphae</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E2D6DE98FDFAFB5F" box="[389,586,1178,1204]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">brilliant granules</emphasis>
absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3079AC0FFE95F59E3EEDEBDFC42FA83" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA2C94BFFE95F59E3EEDEBDFC42FA83" blockId="15.[136,1452,782,1385]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Notes:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB2C8FFE95F59E271DEBCFDFDFB33" box="[290,589,1214,1240]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Entolomataceae" genus="Entoloma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="cyanomelaenum">
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E271DEBCFDFDFB33" box="[290,589,1214,1240]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Entoloma cyanomelaenum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses larger (9–11 × 5.5–6.5 μm) spores and its pileus turns red in KOH (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CB4BAFFE95F59E3DCDEE0FE9DFB17" author="Boedijn, K. B." box="[143,301,1250,1276]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="396 - 439" refId="ref8890" refString="Boedijn, K. B. (1929) Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Pilzflora von Sumatra. Recueil des Travaux Botaniques Neerlandais 26: 396 - 439." type="journal article" year="1929">Boedijn 1929</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CB4BAFFE95F59E269DEE0FE74FB17" author="Horak, E." box="[314,452,1250,1276]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref14097" refString="Horak, E. (1980) Entoloma (Agaricales) in Indomalaya and Australasia. Beihefte Nova Hedwigia vol. 65. J. Cramer, Germany, 352 pp." type="book" year="1980">Horak 1980</bibRefCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB2C8FFE95F59E28ADEE1FDC4FB17" authorityName="Morgan-Jones (1971:" authorityYear="1052" box="[473,628,1250,1276]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Entolomataceae" genus="Entoloma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="gainsvillae">
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E28ADEE1FDC4FB17" box="[473,628,1250,1276]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">E. gainsvillae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has slightly larger spores (8–10 × 6–7 μm) and a smooth pileus (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CB4BAFFE95F59E60ADEE0FF73FACB" author="Murrill, W. A." pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="422 - 433" refId="ref15003" refString="Murrill, W. A. 1943. Some Southern Novelties. Mycologia 35: 422 - 433. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00275514.1943.12017497" type="journal article" year="1943">Murrill 1943</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CB4BAFFE95F59E387DF04FED5FACA" author="Hesler, L. R." box="[212,357,1286,1313]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref14042" refString="Hesler, L. R. (1967) Entoloma in southeastern North America. Beihefte Nova Hedwigia 23, Lubrecht &amp; Cramer, Germany, 195 pp." type="book" year="1967">Hesler 1967</bibRefCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB2C8FFE95F59E22DDF05FE4EFACB" authorityName="Manimohan, Leelavathy &amp; Noordeloos" authorityYear="2002" box="[382,510,1286,1312]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Entolomataceae" genus="Entoloma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="nubilum">
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E22DDF05FE4EFACB" box="[382,510,1286,1312]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">E. nubilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB2C8FFE95F59E1F2DF05FCAEFACB" authorityName="O. V. Morozova, Kovalenko, E. S. Popov &amp; Noordeloos" authorityYear="2022" box="[673,798,1286,1312]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Entolomataceae" genus="Entoloma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="daphnis">
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E1F2DF05FCAEFACB" box="[673,798,1286,1312]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">E. daphnis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by differently-shaped (5–7 angled) spores, a cutis-type pileipellis, and habitat on decaying leaves or on humus (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CB4BAFFE95F59E1ACDF28FBBBFAAF" author="Manimohan, P. &amp; Leelavathy, K. M. &amp; Noordeloos, M. E." box="[767,1035,1322,1348]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="625 - 630" refId="ref14580" refString="Manimohan, P., Leelavathy, K. M. &amp; Noordeloos, M. E. (2002) Three new species of Entoloma from Kerala State, India. Persoonia 17: 625 - 630." type="journal article" year="2002">
Manimohan 
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E0DCDF29FC77FAAF" box="[911,967,1322,1348]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">et al.</emphasis>
2002
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB2C8FFE95F59E74DDF29FB34FAAF" box="[1054,1156,1323,1348]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Entolomataceae" genus="Entoloma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="icarus">
<emphasis id="B9691559FFE95F59E74DDF29FB34FAAF" box="[1054,1156,1323,1348]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">E. icarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses larger (10–13 × 7–9 μm) differently-shaped (with 5–7 sharp angles) spores and cheilocystidia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
